# Internal DNS and IIS Host Header Configuration

## Overview

This phase of the project focused on simplifying access to the osTicket platform by creating an internal DNS record and configuring an IIS website with a host header. This allowed users to access the help desk application using a friendly URL instead of navigating directly to the server IP address or appending `/osTicket` to the URL.

---

## Create DNS Host Record

* Log into `CA-DC-01`

* Open:

  * Server Manager
  * Tools
  * DNS

* Expand:

  * Forward Lookup Zones
  * `woodtech.local`

* Right click:

  * `woodtech.local`

* Select:

  * New Host (A or AAAA)

* Configure:

  * Name: `helpdesk`
  * IP Address: `[CA-DC-01 IP Address]`

* Select:

  * Add Host

* Select:

  * OK

* Verify:

  * `helpdesk.woodtech.local` appears within the `woodtech.local` zone

---

## Verify DNS Resolution

* Log into `desktop01`

* Open:

  * Command Prompt

* Run:

```powershell id="u4mjlwm"
ping helpdesk.woodtech.local
```

* Verify:

  * DNS resolves to the IP address of `CA-DC-01`

---

## Create IIS Website

* Log into `CA-DC-01`

* Open:

  * Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager

* Expand:

  * Sites

* Right click:

  * Sites

* Select:

  * Add Website

* Configure:

  * Site Name: `HelpDesk`
  * Physical Path: `C:\inetpub\wwwroot\osTicket`
  * Type: `http`
  * IP Address: `All Unassigned`
  * Port: `80`
  * Host Name: `helpdesk.woodtech.local`

* Select:

  * OK

* If prompted:

  * "There is already a site using port 80. Do you want to continue?"

* Select:

  * Yes

---

## Configure Default Web Site Binding

* Expand:

  * Sites

* Right click:

  * Default Web Site

* Select:

  * Edit Bindings

* Select:

  * `http`

* Select:

  * Edit

* Configure:

  * Host Name: `ca-dc-01.woodtech.local`

* Select:

  * OK

* Select:

  * Close

---

## Verify Website Access

* Log into `desktop01`

* Open:

  * Web Browser

* Navigate to:

```text
http://helpdesk.woodtech.local
```

* Verify:

  * osTicket User Portal loads successfully

* Navigate to:

```text
http://helpdesk.woodtech.local/scp
```

* Verify:

  * osTicket Staff Control Panel loads successfully

